@database "Improved TextBlock Macro Guide"
@author "Heiko Schr—der"
@$VER: 3.0 (Release 3)
@wordwrap

@node Main "Improved TextBlock V2.1"
                               @{" < Table of Contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

@{fg shine}Benifits:@{fg text}
   How often have you wanted to use more than the normal 37 letter text
   block limits? Some people say, "It gets better with the Text blocks from
   FW97". Of course, the only problem with the new text blocks, is that it
   is so hard to get the knack of using them...

@{fg shine}Requirements:@{fg text}
   NONE.

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview ImprovedTextblock.iff"}:@{fg text}

   First you must press the @{fg fill}TAB@{fg text}-Key to activate the field
   into which, you shall put the text. 
   With this you can use textblocks containing up to 999 characters.

   Entering text from your document:
      Select a piece of text from your document or a previous Textblock
      and activate the Gadget to the left of the textfield. A tick should
      appear and disappear.
      The text, will automatically be inserted into the textfield.
      The style of the text can be altered through the Menu:
      @{fg fill}Project | @{"Preferences..." link "Voreinst"}@{fg text}

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

   @{fg fill}A@{fg text}pply
      An Improved textblock containing your text will be created.

   @{fg fill}R@{fg text}efresh
      This is useful for super long Textblocks. Because the macro uses several
      textblocks grouped together when you turn or enlarge the grouped text-
      blocks the text becomes disjointed, this button overcomes the problem.

   @{fg fill}C@{fg text}ancel
   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or closing the Window.
      Terminates the Macro.

@endnode

@node Voreinst "Preferences for ImprovedTextBlock"

   Selecting this option opens the normal Final Writer Text-Block-Preferences
   window. From here you can set the Typeface specifications for the Textblock.

   Leave the "Content" field free.
   Until the Preferences window is closed the £Apply¨ button will NOT work.

@endnode
